OL,3,CInsurance advice issued for those
OL,4,Caffected by storm damage
OL,6,F"Even if they are not covered we would
OL,7,Fgive them general advice if they are a
OL,8,Fcustomer."
OL,10,FAsked when people could expect works
OL,11,Fto begin on repairs, Stuart said: "It
OL,12,Fwill depend on the extent of damage.
OL,14,F"The industry will be impacted as will
OL,15,Fa lot of adjusters - insurers are
OL,16,Fgoing to be busy. We just ask
OL,17,Fcustomers to bare with us as we
OL,18,Fprocess the claims.
